HIV pixel clustering - iterative clustering (no arcsinh, k=20, z-score cap=2 for hierarchical clustering, iterative z-score threshold=3)

Candace Liu

May 5, 2020

  • Only 1 round of FlowSOM
  • Re-hierarchically cluster only the clusters in large hierarchical clusters
  • FlowSOM cluster pixels in large hierarchical clusters, then re-do hierarchical clusters

Only 1 round of FlowSOM

Re-hierarchically cluster only the clusters in large hierarchical clusters

First count number of clusters in each hierarchical cluster (hCluster) and z-score this count table. For each hCluster that is above some z-score threshold, re-hierarically cluster the clusters in that hCluster, where the number of new hClusters is the count of clusters / median of the count table. Repeat until all z-scores in count table are below the threshold.

FlowSOM cluster pixels in large hierarchical clusters, then re-do hierarchical clusters

First count number of clusters in each hierarchical cluster (hCluster) and z-score this count table. For each hCluster that is above some z-score threshold, run FlowSOM on the pixels in that hCluster. Hierarchically cluster all FlowSOM clusters, where the number of hierarchical clusters is the total number of FlowSOM clusters / median of the count table. Only iterate once for now.
